<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The structure of the excise duty to which the Member States subject manufactured tobacco shall be harmonized in several stages. </inglise>
<eesti> Tubakatoodete aktsiisi struktuur tuleb liikmesriikide vahel harmoneerida j&auml;rk- j&auml;rgult. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive lays down general principles for this harmonization, as well as the special criteria applicable during the stages of harmonization. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas direktiivis tuuakse v&auml;lja harmoneerimise p&otilde;hialused, samuti harmoneerimise eri etappidel rakendatavad erikriteeriumid. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The transition from one stage of harmonization to the next shall be decided on by the Council on a proposal from the Commission, taking into account the effects produced during the stage in progress by the measures introduced by the Member States into their system of excise duties in order to comply with the provisions applicable during that stage. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;lemineku &uuml;helt harmoneerimise etapilt j&auml;rgmisele otsustab komisjon n&otilde;ukogu ettepanekul, v&otilde;ttes arvesse tulemusi, mis on saadud k&auml;imasoleva etapi jooksul meetmete abil, mille liikmesriigid on l&uuml;litanud oma aktsiisis&uuml;steemi, et rakendada k&otilde;nealuse etapi jooksul kohaldatavaid s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise> The transition from one stage to the next may be deferred especially if it is likely to involve disproportionate losses of revenue for a Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;leminekut &uuml;helt staadiumilt teisele v&otilde;ib edasi l&uuml;kata, eriti juhul kui see ilmselt p&otilde;hjustaks liikmesriigile &uuml;lem&auml;&auml;ra suurt eelarvetulude v&auml;henemist. </eesti>
